    "post-quiz-promise": {
      "type": "post-quiz-promise",
      "settings": {
        "banner_alt": "A couple relaxing at home together, laughing and at ease",
        "eyebrow": "Our Promise",
        "heading": "Here is exactly what we stand behind.",
        "content": "<p>Your set is custom-made to your own mouth. We treat the fit as our responsibility, not yours.</p><p>When your veneers arrive, wear them. If the fit is not right, tell us. <strong>We remake it free, up to twice, within 30 days</strong>, with prepaid shipping both ways. We do not consider it finished until it fits.</p><p><strong>You can cancel for a full refund any time before we begin production.</strong> Because each set is made from scratch for your specific anatomy, finished cases cannot be refunded for a change of mind, the same as any custom-made product.</p><p>Before production: change your mind for any reason and pay nothing. After production: we keep refining the fit until it is right. That is the promise a custom product can stand behind.</p>"
      }
    },
    "post_quiz_faq_KBXDLX": {
      "type": "post-quiz-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_wBkQH3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Should I get both arches or a single arch?",
            "answer": "<p>Upper-only veneers can look unnatural when you talk or smile, because your lower teeth show and a color difference between veneered upper teeth and natural lower teeth becomes noticeable. If your lower teeth are already in good shape, a single arch may be all you need. If not, the full set keeps everything consistent. Both arches are $1,994 ($1,894 with your credit) versus $1,297 for a single arch.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_w7PnNF": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is Revive right for me?",
            "answer": "<p>Your quiz answers point to a strong fit. Revive Veneers work well for anyone with healthy teeth and gums who wants to improve the appearance of stained, slightly gapped, or worn teeth. They are not right for people with active gum disease, severe bite issues, multiple missing teeth at the end of the arch, or anyone currently wearing full dentures.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_H9cy8p": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens after I order?",
            "answer": "<p>Your impression kit ships within 48 hours. You take impressions at home (about 5 minutes), mail them back free, and your custom veneers arrive 2 to 3 weeks after we receive them. Every case is built to Dr. Turley's 7-Point Smile Design Protocol. The kit includes two batches of putty, and if your first impressions do not capture enough detail, we send a second kit free before production starts.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_HBpF6m": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I cancel after ordering?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Cancel for a full refund any time before we begin production. Once your case is in production, the 30-Day Fit Remake covers you. If the fit or look is not right, we remake it free, up to twice, within 30 days of delivery. Just email <a href=\"mailto:support@reviveteeth.com\" title=\"mailto:support@reviveteeth.com\">support@reviveteeth.com.</a></p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_j6BbPU": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long do the veneers last?",
            "answer": "<p>With everyday care, Revive Veneers typically last 3 to 5 years. Rinse them after eating, brush them gently, and keep them in their case when they are out. The better you care for them, the longer they last.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_GHAf9e": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I wear them while eating?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes, for everyday soft foods. Revive Veneers are made for daily wear, including eating and drinking. For hard, crunchy, sticky, or very hot foods, take them out first. They are a cosmetic appliance, not a replacement for your natural bite, so they are not built for heavy chewing. Removing them for tougher meals also helps them last longer.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
